[4] USA (California)
Date: 19 Feb 2014
Source: OC Register [edited]
http://www.ocregister.com/articles/measles-602286-cases-health.html


A 4th Orange County resident has been diagnosed with measles since late last year [2013], the Health Care Agency said Tuesday [18 Feb 2014].

The circumstances are still under investigation, but the latest patient, an adult who had been previously vaccinated, had contact with one of the earlier cases, said spokeswoman Nicole Stanfield. Among the earlier cases of 2 adults and one child, one had also been vaccinated.

