[10] Viet Nam
Date: Sat 15 Feb 2014
Source: Nhan Dan, Viet Nam News Agency (VNA) [edited]
http://en.nhandan.org.vn/society/health/item/2313302-numerous-measures-taken-to-contain-measles.html


The Department of Preventive Health under the Ministry of Health on [15 Feb 2014] launched preventive measures against measles, which took the lives of 3 children in the country so far this year [2014].

At an online meeting of the Pasteur Institute in central Nha Trang city and the Central Highlands Institute of Hygiene and Epidemiology, Deputy Health Minister Nguyen Thanh Long confirmed that if preventive measures are fully applied, the measles outbreak will be contained in 2 months.

He asked local authorities nationwide to closely monitor the situation so as to deal promptly with people who contract the disease.

Provinces and cities where measles has been recorded were requested to organise vaccinations for all children under 2 years old who have not been fully vaccinated against the disease.

The National Institute of Hygiene and Epidemiology was asked to ensure that stocks of the vaccine were sufficient.

According to the department, 993 cases have been recorded in 24 provinces and cities so far this year [2014], with one death in Hanoi and 2 in the northern province, Yen Bai.

Largely, the outbreak is isolated to northern mountainous provinces, Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City.

Children not fully vaccinated are currently the most vulnerable group. According to the World Health Organisation (WHO), measles is one of the leading causes of death among young children. The disease, which is caused by a virus of the paramyxovirus family, causes about 330 deaths every day and 14 deaths every hour. Thanks to vaccination, a 78 percent drop has been seen in deaths between 2000 and 2012 worldwide, the organisation pointed out. Since 2000, more than one billion children in high risk countries were immunised against the disease through mass vaccination programmes.

--
