[11] Australia
Date: 20 Feb 2014
Source: Bayside Bulletin [edited]
http://www.baysidebulletin.com.au/story/2101672/health-officials-warn-of-measles-outbreak/?cs=213


Queensland Health is warning of a possible measles outbreak after a man with the virus travelled from North Stradbroke Island to Cleveland on 12 Feb 2014.

Metro South Health's public health unit issued the notification on Tuesday [18 Feb 2014] of the 2nd measles case from the island in a month. Queensland Health spokesman said a man, who did not know he had the virus, left North Stradbroke Island on the 7.30 am water taxi to the mainland on Wed 12 Feb 2014 and returned on the 10.55 am water taxi.

Public health physician Dr Kari Jarvinen said residents needed to be alert for symptoms, particularly those who could have had contact with the man. The island was put on alert on 24 Jan 2014 after a man with measles caught a 5 pm barge that day.

