[Among the most contagious vaccine preventable diseases, measles continues to be a serious problem globally, causing considerable morbidity, mortality, and consumption of public health and medical resources. The factors responsible for this include the inadequacy of immunization programs in low-resource areas, less than complete immunity in some individuals afforded even by 2 doses of measles-containing vaccines, high levels of global travel, and ironically, diminished acceptance of immunization in developed countries. - Mod.LM]
